Chat Analyzer

Personal Project

Chat Analyzer is a tool used to process and analyze chat data from past live streams, providing summarized information about chat activity over the stream’s lifetime.

This was my first-ever released python package, and I'm still working on it! Next in the pipeline is using NLP to intelligently classify the highlighted sections of stream.

ForeverFan

Developer

ForeverFan is a service that allows musical artists to accumulate a fanbase that automatically pre-saves all of their future releases. It currently services artists with 60-900,000 monthly listeners.

I'm currently working as the Lead Frontend Developer, using{" "} Airbnb's visx library {" "} to build artist-facing analytics pages.

WeScheme

Intern @ Bootstrap

Bootstrap {" "} creates research-based, integrated Computer Science and Data Science modules for Math, Science, Business and Social Studies classes grades 5-12. WeScheme is a browser-based Racket compiler used as part of the curriculum.

I'm currently working to refactor the entire application using ReactJS to support modern browsers and significantly increase codebase maintainability.

Applying Arrow’s Impossibility Theorem

Class Group Project (Brown University)

CSCI 1710: Logic for Systems is a course that explores using mathematical logic to reason about systems and discovering whether their behavior meets our expectations.

As a final project, my group of three decided to model a simple plurality and ranked-choice voting system, and demonstrated the satisfiability and validity of the three components of{" "} Arrow’s Impossibility Theorem {" "} in each of the modeled voting systems.
